<li id="cite_note-angular-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-angular_19-0" title="">^</a></b> In particular, the angular rate appearing in the polar coordinate expressions is that of the particle under observation, <img class="tex" alt="\dot{\theta}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/a/d/5ad3b29a9f6667a8a71e8465809d09e8.png" />, while that in classical Newtonian mechanics is the angular rate Ω of a rotating frame of reference.</li>
